.TH man 1 "20 November 2020" "0.20" "HSH man page"
.SH NAME
.B hsh 
- Simple Shell Studying purpose Holberton School
.SH SYNOPSIS
.B ./hsh 
[command] [options] [FILE]
.SH COPYRIGHT
.B hsh 
is on public Domain, no copyright protection.
.SH DESCRIPTION
.B hsh 
(Simple Shell) is an end-of-term project for students at Holberton School,
understand and build a simple, functional shell program.

.B Overview

The simple shell is a simplified iteration of a command line interpreter, similar to 
.B bash
.I FORMAT [ARGUMENT]...
.SH OPTIONS
.B hsh
operates in both 
.I interactive 
and 
.I non-interactive
mode. The user may initiate 
.B simple shell
and begin working or initate 
.B simple shell
using commands meant to be run by the program.
.SH ARGUMENTS
The first argument, argument 0 is understood to be the command to be run by 
.B simple shell
and arguments following as modifiers or options.
.SH INVOCATION
.B hsh
may be invoked with the same functionality in 
.I interactive 
or 
.I non-interactive 
mode.  The user may quit the program by typing "exit", "Ctrl + D",  on the command line.
When a command has been executed, 
.B simple shell 
returns with a new prompt: "$ "

.B Example
.IP

$./hsh

$pwd

Username@your-regular-prompt:~$

$

$/bin/pwd

Username@your-regular-prompt:~$
$

.SH RESERVED WORDS
.B env:
prints the environment variables.

.B cd:
change the current directorie.

.B history:
print last commands.

.B exit:
quits the program, exits the shell.

.SH HISTORY
The 
.B history 
built-in displays the history list, one command per line, preceded with line numbers, starting with 0. On exit the entire history is cleared.
.SH SHELL BUILTIN COMMANDS
The commands 
.B cat
,
.B ls
and
.B echo
are handled automatically by 
.B hsh

.SH BUILTINS
.IP env
Prints out all environment variables
.IP cd
To change directorie
.IP history
Prints the last 100 comands
.IP exit
Exits process and frees memory allocated.

.SH BUGS
No Known bug , please 
